# PIXS Direction Rule

## Product intent

- Build a premium AI pet art studio experience, not a casual filter app.
- Prioritize first-impression impact on the landing page.
- Guide users with theme-card UX instead of free-form prompt writing.

## Brand system

- Tone: premium, dark, classical-modern blend.
- Colors: `#121212` background, `#E1C16E` accent.
- Typography: serif headlines + sans-serif body.

## Main themes

- `The Royal Atelier`: Rembrandt/Vermeer/Van Gogh inspired studio-art mood.
- `Cine-Matic Paw`: Marvel/Disney/cyberpunk inspired cinematic mood.

## Engineering defaults

- Frontend: Next.js App Router + Tailwind CSS.
- Backend: FastAPI.
- AI: Gemini 3 Flash Image API.
- Keep landing sections modular and reusable.
- Avoid unnecessary client components; prefer server components by default.

## Landing must include

- Hero with a strong value proposition and clear CTA.
- Two-concept showcase cards.
- Quality proof (`8k resolution`, `studio lighting`, `sharp focus`).
- Three-step flow explanation (upload -> theme select -> generate).
- Trust/FAQ section and final conversion CTA.
